cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation for object recognition algorithms using synthetic images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel deep generative model to address the domain discrepancy between synthetic and real images, which involves training off-the-shelf classifiers. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves 3D CAD models, which may suggest the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics) as a possibility. Finally, the use of deep neural networks for image synthesis and domain adaptation may suggest the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics and Control) as a possibility.
